<TITLE> Chittagong honours martyred intellectuals </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Dec 14 (bdnews24.com)  The Martyred Intellectuals Day is being observed in Chittagong with rich tributes to the slain members of the intelligentsia in 1971 and call for the trial of war criminals. Different political parties, professionals and social bodies organised programmes including laying of wreaths at the Shaheed Minar, discussion meets and cultural programmes. They also called people not to vote for candidates with links to war crimes. At the initiative of the Chittagong University, a discussion presided by vice-chancellor Dr. M Badiul Alam was arranged at the university library auditorium. President of the Chittagong University Teacher's Club Professor Dr. Kamal Hossain, general secretary Dr. Kamrul Huda and others spoke at the programme. Chittagong Journalists' Union and Chittagong press Club co-organised a discussion meeting. b
